IBM Corporation Extends Smarter Cities Initiative Through Acquisition of Curam Software

Monday, 5 Dec 2011 05:00am EST

IBM Corporation announced that it has signed a definitive agreement to acquire Curam Software Ltd. to help governments improve the efficiency, effectiveness and accessibility of social programs for smarter cities. Financial terms were not disclosed. Curam Software is used in more than 80 government agency projects around the world to provide the most appropriate social programs to citizens and their families in a timely manner, deliver services more effectively and continuously monitor progress toward achieving people's social and economic potential.Â 

